The Attio Model Context Protocol (MCP) server allows AI assistants like Claude and ChatGPT to interact with your Attio CRM workspace using natural language [1][2]. It supports comprehensive CRM operations, including searching, creating, updating, and deleting records (people, companies, deals, lists, tasks, and notes) [1][3].

You have two primary ways to connect:

Official Hosted Server: Use https://mcp.attio.com/mcp as a remote MCP server. It uses OAuth for authentication, so no API keys are required [4][2].

Self-Hosted Implementation: Use the community-maintained package `attio-mcp` (npm install -g attio-mcp). This requires an `ATTIO_API_KEY` and local configuration [5][6].

For Claude Desktop configuration, add the following to your settings:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "attio": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["attio-mcp"],
      "env": {
        "ATTIO_API_KEY": "YOUR_ATTIO_API_KEY"
      }
    }
  }
}
```
